cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.CC, cs.SI, cs.NI. 

The paper deals with the topic of universal security on wire tap networks, which involves information theory, cryptography, and network coding. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces new parameters for code pairs that are linear over the field used in the network, which involves algebraic structures and coding theory, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) possible sub-categories as well.
